#  Spotify Cohort Analysis â€“ User Listening Behavior

##  Problem Statement
Music streaming platforms need to understand how user listening behavior changes over time to improve recommendations and retention.

##  Objective
- Analyze cohort-based listening trends
- Identify patterns in user engagement over time
- Provide insights for personalized music recommendations

##  Dataset
- Source: Spotify song/user dataset
- Data includes user activity, song features, and listening timestamps

##  Tools & Technologies
- Python
- Pandas, NumPy
- Matplotlib, Seaborn
- Jupyter Notebook

##  Project Workflow
1. Data cleaning and formatting
2. Cohort creation based on first activity
3. Retention and engagement analysis
4. Visualization of cohort trends

##  Key Analysis
- Cohort analysis
- Retention matrix
- Time-based engagement tracking

##  Key Insights
- Early cohorts show higher long-term engagement
- User activity drops after initial weeks without personalization
- Certain song features correlate with better retention

##  Visualizations
- Cohort heatmaps
- Retention curves
- Engagement trends

##  Results
This analysis helps identify when users disengage and highlights opportunities to improve recommendation strategies.


